28/09/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian Justice Ministry announced Saturday (27 September) it would send a request to Bosnia and Herzegovina for the extradition of Igor Mikola to stand trial in Croatia. Mikola is serving a 27-month prison sentence in the Bosnian town of Zenica for attempted extortion. The Zagreb County Court launched a trial against Mikola a year ago, indicting him for war crimes committed in the Pakrac area in 1991. (HINA - 27/09/03)
